Listen to the four versions of the new Czech national anthem.
On the occasion of the Czech Republic's Statehood Day, Prime Minister Mirek Topolánek presented the new recordings of the national anthem, Where is my homeland, in a ceremony on Sunday.
The anthem was newly recorded by the National Theatre Orchestra under the direction of Jiří Bělohlávek.
There are four versions available - with male or female solo singing, in choral version and in an instrumental version.
The song was written by Kateřina Kněžínková and Adam Plachetka.
The editors of the hymn versions are Otakar Jeremiáš and Jaroslav Krček.
The iHNed.cz server allows you to listen to all four versions at once.
For Bělohlávek, the Czech national anthem is one of the most beautiful hymns.
