"From the beginning, I tried to keep a clear diction with both of them and then with the choir, so that the text could be understood well, so that harmony could be created", says the conductor.
The Czech national anthem will be celebrating its 175th anniversary next year.
The song Kde domov můj was first heard in 1834 on the stage of the State Theatre in the original Czech play Fidlovačka by Josef Kajetán Tyl, the music was by František Škroup.
It became popular, and people spontaneously adopted it.
The first stanza of the song became an organic part of the national anthem after the formation of Czechoslovakia in 1918.
It remained one of the seven state symbols even after the formation of the independent Czech Republic.
