If we cannot be part of Germany or Austria, we at least want to live under the auspices of the United States of America.
It is with this wish that some groups of Sudeten Germans are said to have approached the US president in 1945.
This is shown, among other things, by a letter that has been preserved in a private archive and is now in the collections of the South Bohemian Scientific Library.
