Inspired by Benito Pérez Galdós's Episodios Nacionales, José Luis Carci's Sangre de Mayo is a revised version of the famous Spanish revolt against the French, a film that is admirable in its cinematography, with an investment of around 15 million euros in the filming.
In this way, the cineast has tried to 'represent a lot of personalities and social analysis' that he has always admired in the works of the famous novelist, Carci explained today at the presentation of the film with Quim Gutiérrez and Paula Echevarría at the beginning of a long list of actors.
