Many of the actors he meets in 'Sangre de mayo' have to rehearse in front of his camera, as in the case of Miguel Rellán, Carlos Larrañaga or Fernando Guillén Cuervo.
Garci, who has been nominated for four Oscars (one of which he won), said that none of the three candidates representing Spain at the Academy of Hollywood this year represent a younger generation of Spanish filmmaking: neither "Sangre de mayo", "Siete mesas de billar francés" and finally, the selected film "Los girasoles ciegos".
