Prices for electricity, gas, steam and water rose by 18.7 percent compared with the previous year.
In the domestic market, the highest price increase was recorded in August in the capital goods sector (0.7%).
Prices in the consumer goods production sectors rose by 0.3%, while they remained the same in the energy and refining sectors compared with the previous month.
The largest price increase in August 2008 compared to the 2007 period was observed in the energy and recycling sector (16.8%).
In the consumer goods sector, prices rose by 6.8%, while in the capital goods sector prices fell by 1.4%.
Export prices of manufactured goods measured in forint rose by 1.1% in August compared with the previous month, but fell by 3.9% year on year.
